Project description

PBLib Python3 Bindings

Authors

Logic Optimization Group @ University of Lleida

  • Carlos Ansótegui

  • Toni Pacheco

  • Josep Pon

Requirements

The only requirement is a C/C++ compiler with C++11 support that can beaccessed by distutil/setuptools.

Documentation

The online documentation can be found here: http://ulog.udl.cat/static/doc/pypblib/html/index.html

The API is documented using Sphinx, to build it: download the source filesopen a terminal in the Doc directory and type:

$ make html or $ make latexpdf

Installation

To install the python module use the setup.py script located in the root of theproject or (preferably) the pip3 package manager.

$ python3 setup.py install or pip3 install .

If you don’t have admin privileges or just prefere to isntall the pacakge foryour user only, add the –user flag to any of the commands above.

Project Structure

  • Doc: sphinx source code and scripts to build the documentation.

  • External: C/C++ source code of third-party libraries.

  • Modules: C/C++ code of the Python C-Extensions.
